description._content: Creator: Unidentified Location: Queensland, Australia Description: Justin Fox Greenlaw Foxton was born in Melbourne on 24 September 1847. He was eduacted at the Melbourne Church of England Grammar School and went to Brisbane when he was fifteen. He was articled to M. Thompson, solicitor, at Ipswich and was admitted to the bar when he was twenty-two. He practiced as a solicitor in Stanthorpe and then came to Brisbane and went into partnership with J. M. Thompson. In 1883 he was elected to the legislative assembly as member for Carnarvon and held this seat until 1904. Defeated in the 1904 elections he entered federal politics as a member for Brisbane in the house of representatives in 1906 and was minister without portfolio in the third Deakin ministry from June 1909 to April 1910 when he was defeated at the general election. He died in Brisbane on 23 June 1916.
